{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "name": "Pandu AI Assistant",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "A draggable AI assistant that works on any website.",
  "permissions": [
    "activeTab",
    "scripting"
  ],
  "background": {
    "service_worker": "background.js"
  },
  "action": {
    "default_icon": "icon.png",
    "default_title": "Open Pandu AI"
  },
  "icons": {
    "48": "icon.png"
  }
}```

*You'll also need a simple icon file (e.g., `icon.png` of 48x48 pixels) in the same folder.*

#### **3. Create a `background.js` File**

This script will listen for a click on the extension's icon and inject the assistant into the current page.

```javascript
chrome.action.onClicked.addListener((tab) => {
  chrome.scripting.executeScript({
    target: { tabId: tab.id },
    files: ['content.js']
  });
  chrome.scripting.insertCSS({
    target: { tabId: tab.id },
    files: ['pandu.css']
  });
});
